    <sec id="sec4">
      <title>2.2. Models for MSI calling</title>
      <p>MSIsensor performed standard chi-square testing for each site in paired tumor and normal specimens to measure the goodness of fit between the respective allele frequency distributions [<xref rid="ref38" ref-type="bibr">38</xref>], with the chi-square test p-value subsequently used to classify the stability of distribution in tumor [<xref rid="ref18" ref-type="bibr">18</xref>, <xref rid="ref39" ref-type="bibr">39</xref>]. In this study, allele frequency distributions and p-values of microsatellites in each original TCGA sample were obtained using MSIsensor.</p>
      <p>There were over 2.7 billion allele frequency distributions of 1763,163 microsatellites obtained from 1565 tumor samples. Here, the p-value was used to identify the stability of each distribution for the subsequent machine learning step. The stability of a distribution was labeled as âunstableâ for p-value &lt;0.05, otherwise âstableâ.</p>
